The paper deals with problems related to visibility graphs of points, segments, and polygons, which are fundamental concepts in computational geometry. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also discusses open problems and conjectures, which are related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves graph theory (cs.GR) and combinatorics (cs.CC) as the visibility graph is a graph-theoretic concept, and the problems discussed in the paper are related to combinatorial optimization.
